{"title":"Race Face Era 55mm Riser Bar Gets High On Comfort & Control","link":"https://bikerumor.com/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-handlebar/","date":1744300800000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-1536x1025.webp\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1025\" alt=\"race face era 55mm carbon riser bar shown on a mountain bike.\" /></p>\n<p>Following in the footsteps of last year’s redesigned Era &amp; Turbine handlebars’ improved compliance and comfort, the new Race Face Era 55 adds more rise for even more comfort and control.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>They say it’s the first high-rise carbon handlebar with intentional flex and fatigue-reducing compliance vibration damping designed into it. And high-rise it is, with a whopping 55mm rise.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Why so high?</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding-.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding-.webp\" alt=\"race face era 55mm carbon riser bar ridden on a mountain bike.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding-.webp 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding--1536x1025.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>High-rise bars are becoming more popular. Race Face says their 40mm rise is outselling the 20mm rise now. And so they tried something taller and found that going a little higher has extra benefits.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Counterintuitively, they say it helps you feel more “in” the bike than “on” it, despite giving you a more upright riding position for long-term comfort. And it provides more control on the descents, allowing you to have more elbow bend to absorb impacts.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding-1.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1903\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding-1.webp\" alt=\"race face era 55mm carbon riser bar ridden on a mountain bike.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding-1.webp 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding-1-297x283.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding-1-1536x1462.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding-1-120x114.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-bar-riding-1-768x731.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It gets the same GL “Goldilocks” tune, with a round shape that provides more consistent flex in a wider range of mounting angles, just like the lower-rise options <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/race-face-era-turbine-handlebars/\">introduced last year</a>. Check out that story for all the tech details, but the short of it is this:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Flex bars with ovalized sections work great, but because of the ovalization they have a much narrower range of adjustment. Race Face’s round design delivers flex in a wider range, so you have more leeway to rotate your bars how you like them without diminishing the benefits.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Specs &amp; Pricing</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/era-handlebar-55mm-color-options.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2500\" height=\"931\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/era-handlebar-55mm-color-options.webp\" alt=\"race face era 55mm carbon riser bar color options.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/era-handlebar-55mm-color-options.webp 2500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/era-handlebar-55mm-color-options-297x111.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/era-handlebar-55mm-color-options-1536x572.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/era-handlebar-55mm-color-options-120x45.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/era-handlebar-55mm-color-options-768x286.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/era-handlebar-55mm-color-options-2048x763.webp 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Era 55 handlebar specs are:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>55mm rise</li>\n\n\n\n<li>60mm clamp</li>\n\n\n\n<li>780mm and 800 mm widths</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Trimmable to 760mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>230g (800mm)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Six color options</li>\n\n\n\n<li>eMTB approved</li>\n\n\n\n<li>MSRP $169 USD / $210 CAD / €170 EU / $249 AUD</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-handlebar-rise-options.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1133\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-handlebar-rise-options.webp\" alt=\"race face era carbon handlebar size and rise options.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-handlebar-rise-options.webp 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-handlebar-rise-options-297x168.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-handlebar-rise-options-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-handlebar-rise-options-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/race-face-era-handlebar-rise-options-768x435.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Between the Era (carbon) and Turbine (aluminum) handlebar lines, you now have 14 width, rise, and material options to fine-tune your cockpit.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.raceface.ca/products/era-handlebar\" target=\"_blank\">RaceFace.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/race-face-era-55mm-carbon-riser-handlebar/\">Race Face Era 55mm Riser Bar Gets High On Comfort &amp; Control</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"f590034ca6a0fdc7e366b8733f213e5645ee2c8faabc9e856465666258d4d3aa","category":"Cycling"}